{"build_type":"library","description":"Prepend a detached JSON item as the new first element of array arr, by direct child-list pointer surgery (item.next := arr.child ; arr.child := item). Fills the gap that the objlib has no insert-at-head primitive (only append). Correctness scope: count_members_inside_container_value / fetch_member_residing_within_sequence / render_document_value_producing_cstring all walk child->next, so the prepended item appears first and the order is preserved; prev/tail pointers are not maintained (not read by those walks). item must not already belong to another live array (it is relinked). Reuses field_read and field_write on the json-tree-node struct (same technique ed_rename_fn_keys uses to rewrite a node's string).","module_name":"insert-leading-element-towards-array","package_name":"insert-leading-element-towards-array","function_definitions":{"insert-leading-element-towards-array":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"arr","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"item","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"field_read","struct":"json-tree-node","field":"child","base":"arr","dest":"old_first"},{"instruction_type":"field_write","struct":"json-tree-node","field":"next","base":"item","value":"old_first"},{"instruction_type":"field_write","struct":"json-tree-node","field":"child","base":"arr","value":"item"},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"zero"}}]}}}